00:05:36.420 --> 00:05:38.930
Amazing heart these people
have to adopt a child.

00:05:38.930 --> 00:05:40.540
And they adopted this
little girl from China,

00:05:40.540 --> 00:05:42.930
and they said that she doesn't sleep well.

00:05:42.930 --> 00:05:43.910
And obviously people said,

00:05:43.910 --> 00:05:45.130
well did you try sleeping with her,

00:05:45.130 --> 00:05:48.124
is it neglect, is she just stressed out?

00:05:48.124 --> 00:05:49.960
The parents said, no,
we'll sleep with her.

00:05:49.960 --> 00:05:51.700
And a common question,
something you can think

00:05:51.700 --> 00:05:53.603
about yourself when you interact with,

00:05:54.520 --> 00:05:55.910
especially with younger children,

00:05:55.910 --> 00:05:57.190
if they have poor sleep, you can ask,

00:05:57.190 --> 00:05:59.960
does the problem get better
or worse or stay the same

00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:02.550
if they sleep with the
parents or their caretakers?

00:06:02.550 --> 00:06:03.890
And usually, if it's a behavioral issue,

00:06:03.890 --> 00:06:06.580
if they sleep with the
parents, it gets better.

00:06:06.580 --> 00:06:08.290
Little kids usually wanna be with people

00:06:08.290 --> 00:06:10.020
that love them and protect them.

00:06:10.020 --> 00:06:13.220
But this little girl slept just
as poorly with the parents,

00:06:13.220 --> 00:06:14.820
the adoptive parents.

00:06:14.820 --> 00:06:16.460
In fact, they said, we
wish she'd sleep with us.

00:06:16.460 --> 00:06:17.620
It was an Asian family,

00:06:17.620 --> 00:06:18.453
they said we'd like to sleep with her,

00:06:18.453 --> 00:06:19.640
it's in our culture,

00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:22.211
but we can't sleep with
her, she moves too much.

00:06:22.211 --> 00:06:23.690
So I said, you know,

00:06:23.690 --> 00:06:24.911
there's not many other things it could be

00:06:24.911 --> 00:06:25.930
to differentiate a diagnosis,

00:06:25.930 --> 00:06:28.680
